---
title: Kids’ Cheesy Pepperoni Roll-ups with Ranch Dipper, Apple, Cucumber, & Dried Fruit Mix
description: A tasty, balanced kids’ lunch in 15 minutes? That may sound like a dream, but we’re bringing it to life! You’ll roll up easy-melting shredded mozzarella and zingy pepperoni in flour tortillas, then sizzle them in a hot pan until crispy. Serve the roll-ups with juicy apple slices, crisp cucumber wheels, a chewy-sweet dried fruit medley, and a buttermilk ranch dipper. The kicker? You’ll spend less time shopping, planning, and cooking for your family, and more time hanging out with them!

This recipe is designed to provide lunch for multiple days. For each lunch meal, 3 servings and 6 servings are provided for a 2 person and 4 person box respectively.
